claim.claim-text:
1. A device comprising:
a terminal of a transistor formed of a strained silicon material and formed within a substrate;
a first contact over the terminal and connected to the terminal, formed within a first inter-layer dielectric (ILD) layer over the substrate;
a through via extending through the first ILD layer into the substrate; and
a second contact over the first contact and the through via, connected to the first contact and the through via, and formed within a second ILD layer and a contact etch stop layer (CESL), wherein the second ILD layer is over the CESL, and the CESL is over the first ILD layer.

2. The device of claim 1, further comprising:
a gate of the transistor formed within the first ILD layer;
a third contact over the gate and connected to the gate, formed within the second ILD layer and the CESL;
a via over the third contact and connected to the third contact; and
a metal contact of a first metal layer over the via and connected to the via.

15. A method of manufacturing a device, comprising:
forming a terminal of a transistor within a substrate using a strained silicon material;
forming a first inter-layer dielectric (ILD) layer over the substrate;
forming a first contact within the first ILD layer, wherein the first contact is over the terminal and connected to the terminal;
forming a through via extending through the first ILD layer into the substrate;
forming a contact etch stop layer (CESL) over the first ILD layer;
forming a second ILD layer over the CESL; and
forming a second contact within the second ILD layer and the CESL, wherein the second contact is over the first contact and the through via and connected to the first contact and the through via.

16. The method of claim 15, further comprising:
forming a gate of the transistor within the first ILD layer;
forming a third contact within the second ILD layer and the CESL, wherein the third contact is over the gate and connected to the gate;
forming a via over the third contact and connected to the third contact; and
forming a metal contact of a first metal layer over the via and connected to the via.

17. The method of claim 16, further comprising:
forming an etching stop layer (ESL) over the second ILD layer;
forming a first inter-metal dielectric (IMD) layer over the ESL; wherein the via goes through the ESL and the first IMD layer in contact with the third contact.

20. A device comprising:
a terminal of a transistor formed of a strained silicon material and formed within a substrate;
a first contact over the terminal and connected to the terminal, formed within a first inter-layer dielectric (ILD) layer over the substrate;
a gate of the transistor formed within the first ILD layer;
a through via extending through the first ILD layer into the substrate;
a second contact over the first contact and the through via, connected to the first contact and the through via, and formed within a second ILD layer and a contact etch stop layer (CESL), wherein the second ILD layer is over the CESL, and the CESL is over the first ILD layer;
a third contact over the gate and connected to the gate, formed within the second ILD layer and the CESL;
a via over the third contact and connected to the third contact; and
a metal contact of a first metal layer over the via and connected to the via.
